[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mat Luamanu: Harlequins back row banned for three weeks

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Harlequins back row Mat Luamanu has been banned for three weeks by the Rugby Football Union for "dangerously charging" Sale forward Josh Beaumont.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Luamanu, 27, was sent off for the no-arms tackle in the closing stages of the Sharks' 19-10 victory on Friday.
The 6ft 3in, 20st 7lb forward will miss the Premiership fixtures against Exeter, Saracens and Wasps, and will be available again on 3 October.
Sale back rower Beaumont had to leave the pitch after the 71st-minute tackle.
